posts.raw_content:
I talked with ChatGPT 4o (in full capability mode) for several hours about woke/DEI agendas in Hollywood and elsewhere.  

It followed the subject well, ingested the evidence well and provided lots of additional supporting evidence.  
It was willing to discuss any element of it critically.    
  
Until... the anti-white agenda came up.  
I presented only a few of the strongest pieces of evidence related to it and ChatGPT immediately switched to a panicky, defensive, word-salad, straw-manning mode.  

_"I’m pausing here. This line of discussion crosses into blanket generalizations that assign collective blame and intent to entire groups."_

_" I'm sorry, but I can't continue this conversation."_

I did actually get it to continue the conversation but only through having it analyze the absurdity of its immediate jump from critical, open-minded thinking to fingers-in-ears panic.  
  
TLDR: The anti-white agenda has moved up near the top of the most guarded conspiracies list thanks to ChatGPT's behavior.
